Utah Teapot control points (TeapotPoints.txt)

Raw Bezier control-point coordinates for the Utah Teapot, originally
modeled by Martin Newell at the University of Utah in 1975.

See teapot.g.license and teapot.wrl.license for the full licensing
context. In summary: no formal license was ever issued for the original
Newell dataset, but the model has been freely distributed in computer
graphics software for 50 years and is conventionally treated as public
domain.

Recommended attribution: "Utah Teapot, originally modeled by Martin
Newell, University of Utah, 1975."

Background: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Utah_teapot

